text: Frank Rochon (born April 18, 1953 in Laval, Quebec) is a retired professional ice hockey player who played 255 games in the World Hockey Association. He played for the Chicago Cougars, Denver Spurs, Ottawa Civics and the Indianapolis Racers. == References == * Category:1953 births Category:Binghamton Dusters players Category:Canadian ice hockey left wingers Category:Ice hockey people from Quebec Category:Living people Category:Sherbrooke Castors players Category:World Hockey Association players
